WEBVTT

1
00:00:49,030 --> 00:00:52,132
<i>[man] The Pacific Ocean</i>
<i>between California and Hawaii</i>

2
00:00:52,233 --> 00:00:56,687
<i>is the loneliest stretch</i>
<i>of water in the world.</i>

3
00:00:56,788 --> 00:01:01,942
<i>A century ago, this was a
rarely-traveled route to paradise.</i>

4
00:01:02,043 --> 00:01:06,663
<i>Now it's a race course for the
Indianapolis 500 of the open ocean.</i>

5
00:01:06,764 --> 00:01:12,686
<i>An athletic test of speed and
endurance known as the Transpac.</i>

6
00:01:15,222 --> 00:01:17,240
<i>Roy Disney knows</i>
<i>these waters well,</i>

7
00:01:17,341 --> 00:01:19,609
<i>with two wins and two</i>
<i>record-breaking passages</i>

8
00:01:19,710 --> 00:01:22,379
<i>over the course</i>
<i>of 16 Transpacs.</i>

9
00:01:22,546 --> 00:01:25,515
<i>Now he's giving the next</i>
<i>generation an opportunity</i>

10
00:01:25,616 --> 00:01:27,768
<i>by offering a bunch of rookies</i>
<i>the chance of a lifetime.</i>

11
00:01:27,869 --> 00:01:32,455
<i>Thirty hopefuls were chosen to try
out for a new Transpac campaign</i>

12
00:01:32,557 --> 00:01:35,525
<i>to be called the</i> Morning Light.

13
00:01:36,092 --> 00:01:39,789
<i>A team of judges pushed them</i>
<i>hard for a week,</i>

14
00:01:39,829 --> 00:01:43,230
<i>and by the end the 15 best</i>
<i>and brightest had emerged.</i>

15
00:01:43,266 --> 00:01:45,007
[man] We think you ought
to come to Hawaii.

16
00:01:45,101 --> 00:01:47,431
- No way!
- Whoo!

17
00:01:47,470 --> 00:01:50,268
<i>The 15 sailors will</i>
<i>train for six months</i>

18
00:01:50,306 --> 00:01:53,070
<i>in the big winds</i>
<i>and big seas off Hawaii</i>

19
00:01:53,109 --> 00:01:57,409
<i>before choosing a crew of 11 to race</i>
<i>from California to Diamond Head.</i>

20
00:01:57,447 --> 00:01:59,574
<i>They will face more than 70 competitors,</i>

21
00:01:59,615 --> 00:02:03,642
<i>and they'll try to match the legendary</i>
<i>crew of</i> Argonaut <i>from 1969,</i>

22
00:02:03,686 --> 00:02:07,486
<i>another bunch of teenagers</i>
<i>who borrowed their dad's boat</i>

23
00:02:07,523 --> 00:02:09,582
<i>and won it all.</i>

24
00:02:09,625 --> 00:02:12,492
<i>This is the story of</i> Morning Light.

25
00:02:24,107 --> 00:02:26,302
<i>[man] This is gonna be my first story.</i>

26
00:02:28,611 --> 00:02:31,171
<i>This is gonna be an epic story.</i>

27
00:02:32,415 --> 00:02:35,009
<i>This is gonna probably</i>
<i>be my favorite story.</i>

28
00:02:35,051 --> 00:02:38,680
<i>How it all began for Jesse Fielding</i>
<i>on the ocean, hopefully...</i>

29
00:02:38,721 --> 00:02:42,157
