00:31:03,558 --> 00:31:05,082
<i>chosen team members one by one.</i>

475
00:31:05,126 --> 00:31:08,027
<i>I can't describe how stressful it was.</i>

476
00:31:08,062 --> 00:31:11,554
Two watch captains
would be you and Schubert.

477
00:31:11,599 --> 00:31:14,534
<i>Underneath the skipper</i>
<i>are the watch captains.</i>

478
00:31:14,569 --> 00:31:17,367
<i>They are essentially</i>
<i>the skipper of their watch.</i>

479
00:31:18,673 --> 00:31:21,699
<i>Not only was I not a key player,</i>

480
00:31:21,742 --> 00:31:23,642
<i>I was now sitting, sweating,</i>

481
00:31:23,678 --> 00:31:25,578
<i>hoping just to still make the team.</i>

482
00:31:30,852 --> 00:31:33,719
<i>[Brant-Zawadzki] Every person</i>
<i>on this team deserves to race.</i>

483
00:31:33,754 --> 00:31:36,985
<i>Even if I am lucky enough</i>
<i>to actually go on the race,</i>

484
00:31:37,024 --> 00:31:39,185
<i>it would be hard for me to know</i>
<i>that I'd be taking the place</i>

485
00:31:39,227 --> 00:31:42,162
<i>of someone else</i>
<i>who absolutely deserved to go.</i>

486
00:31:42,196 --> 00:31:45,222
Graham doesn't have
a lot of hours sailing.

487
00:31:45,266 --> 00:31:48,758
If we choose him, we'll have to put
a lot of hours into him.

488
00:31:48,803 --> 00:31:50,100
Mm-hmm.

489
00:31:50,137 --> 00:31:53,368
Right, Robbie knows his bow team.

490
00:31:53,407 --> 00:31:56,672
He knows who he wants to get backed up.
We need him in here for this decision.

491
00:31:56,711 --> 00:31:58,872
[Brant-Zawadzki] How long do you
think this is gonna take tonight?

492
00:31:58,913 --> 00:32:01,541
- Hours.
- [Brant-Zawadzki] When did we start?

493
00:32:01,582 --> 00:32:03,812
- [Branning] I think it's going quick.
- Yeah.

494
00:32:03,851 --> 00:32:06,081
- Seven-thirty-ish?
- [Brant-Zawadzki] It's 9:10 now.

495
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:09,055
Turtle, you've gotta be here
because you...

496
00:32:09,090 --> 00:32:11,888
That's... It's the front of your boat
and we gotta know...

497
00:32:11,926 --> 00:32:14,895
<i>Robbie Kane was next to go in,</i>
<i>and then Jesse made it.</i>

498
00:32:14,929 --> 00:32:18,296
We, uh... We want you on the boat
for the Transpac.

499
00:32:18,332 --> 00:32:20,664
- You all right? [laughs]
- Yeah, I'm fine, dude.

500
00:32:20,701 --> 00:32:22,225
I'm focused in, man.

501
00:32:22,270 --> 00:32:24,033
[chuckles]

502
00:32:24,071 --> 00:32:26,767
<i>[Brant-Zawadzki] Towiller got called in,</i>
<i>and that left four spots,</i>

503
00:32:26,807 --> 00:32:28,741
<i>with eight of us still waiting.</i>

504
00:32:28,776 --> 00:32:31,267
[Wilmot] We think
you got a great personality.

505
00:32:31,312 --> 00:32:33,542
We think you're very focused.

506
00:32:33,581 --> 00:32:36,311
And you can drive a boat very nicely.

507
00:32:36,350 --> 00:32:37,374
Thanks.

508
00:32:38,553 --> 00:32:40,748
[Wilmot] We've kept her
out of here for a reason.

509
00:32:42,023 --> 00:32:44,583
We can't hold her back.
She's on our boat.

510
00:32:44,625 --> 00:32:46,718
Come on, you injured soldier.

511
00:32:47,862 --> 00:32:50,626
<i>[Tulloch] The relief on my face</i>
<i>must have been palpable.</i>

512
00:32:50,665 --> 00:32:52,132
<i>They still wanted me.</i>

513
00:32:52,166 --> 00:32:54,293
[Wilmot] We expect you to heal,
not break any more arms.

514
00:32:54,335 --> 00:32:56,132
- No more skiing, snowboarding.
- No more skiing.

515
00:32:56,637 --> 00:32:58,662
<i>[Brant-Zawadzki]</i>
<i>Chris Welch followed Genny.</i>

516
00:32:58,706 --> 00:33:00,333
Awesome. I'm in.

517
00:33:00,374 --> 00:33:02,137
Sign me up! [laughs]

518
00:33:02,176 --> 00:33:04,508
- [Wilmot] Do you want to... Yeah?
- Oh, yeah! Yeah!

519
00:33:04,545 --> 00:33:06,775
<i>[Brant-Zawadzki]</i>
<i>And finally Branning was called in.</i>

520
00:33:08,649 --> 00:33:11,413
- [Wilmot] How is it out there?
- [Branning] Quiet.

521
00:33:15,723 --> 00:33:18,954
<i>[Brant-Zawadzki] Five of us were left in</i>
<i>the kitchen waiting for one more spot.</i>

522
00:33:22,196 --> 00:33:25,495
OK, guys, everyone else.
OK, guys.

523
00:33:26,467 --> 00:33:28,025
So, we brought you all in.

524
00:33:29,370 --> 00:33:32,100
At the end of the day,
we all are the...

